description:
Wu-Tang Clan's RZA and Ghostface Killah raise the stakes in issue four as the gangster thread and horror thread coalesce! The deaths grow more gruesome, the gangsters more brutal, the mysteries more intriguing... and The Ghostface Killah rises!

Note: This issue was released a week early by the publisher (11/6/2013).

An explosive new take on the hit TV show AIRWOLF from Lion Forge Comics! When the clandestine organization known as the FIRM contracts DR. CHARLES HENRY MOFFIT to create the ultimate first strike weapon, a helicopter code-named AIRWOLF, little do they realize it will be their undoing. As the Firm stands poised to commission an entire fleet of Airwolves it is betrayed when Moffit steals the superweapon for himself and leaves pilots CAPTAIN STRINGFELLOW HAWKE and LIEUTENANT DOMINIC SANTINI to take the fall. Even though these two soldiers find themselves weaponless they are certainly not out of the fight!
name: Chapter 1

Everything’s going fine until a squad of gun-toting mercenaries crashes their party.

By Daniel Way and Shawn Crystal!

description:
Zegas #0 is the latest edition of short stories featuring the Zegas siblings, Emily & Boston, written, drawn and colored by cartoonist Michel Fiffe. This Zero Issue contains previously released work via webcomics: "Birthday", "Cactus" and a couple more extra bits - the majority presented in print for the very first time. It's how the stories were initially designed to be seen, and since they're no longer available digitally they can exclusively be read here.

Just like the first two issues, Zegas #0 is a full color magazine-size comic book, 24 pages, signed by Fiffe, limited to 400 copies.
